WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:14.910 align:middle line:90%


00:00:14.910 --> 00:00:18.389 align:middle line:90%
[RUMBLING]

00:00:18.389 --> 00:00:26.341 align:middle line:90%


00:00:26.341 --> 00:00:29.820 align:middle line:90%
[HUMMING]

00:00:29.820 --> 00:00:32.310 align:middle line:90%


00:00:32.310 --> 00:00:36.330 align:middle line:84%
>> I was conscious
in my mother's womb,

00:00:36.330 --> 00:00:39.700 align:middle line:84%
feeling the movements
in her body,

00:00:39.700 --> 00:00:43.085 align:middle line:90%
aware of my own helpless state.

00:00:43.085 --> 00:00:46.390 align:middle line:90%


00:00:46.390 --> 00:00:49.330 align:middle line:90%
[HEARTBEAT]

00:00:49.330 --> 00:00:52.270 align:middle line:90%
[RUMBLING]

00:00:52.270 --> 00:01:01.290 align:middle line:84%
This body, bundle of bones,
is not I. Occasionally,

00:01:01.290 --> 00:01:05.129 align:middle line:84%
the darkness of the womb
would be disappeared,

00:01:05.129 --> 00:01:06.770 align:middle line:90%
and light would visit me.

00:01:06.770 --> 00:01:10.710 align:middle line:90%


00:01:10.710 --> 00:01:15.430 align:middle line:84%
On one side, I wanted to
express myself as a human being.

00:01:15.430 --> 00:01:19.290 align:middle line:84%
Yet, on the other
side, I didn't,

00:01:19.290 --> 00:01:23.124 align:middle line:90%
because I felt I was spirit.

00:01:23.124 --> 00:01:26.596 align:middle line:90%
[RUMBLING]

00:01:26.596 --> 00:01:28.580 align:middle line:90%


00:01:28.580 --> 00:01:32.052 align:middle line:90%
[CHATTER]

00:01:32.052 --> 00:01:35.050 align:middle line:90%


00:01:35.050 --> 00:01:38.590 align:middle line:90%
I see behind the scenes.

00:01:38.590 --> 00:01:41.420 align:middle line:90%
The visible man is a shadow.

00:01:41.420 --> 00:01:44.000 align:middle line:90%


00:01:44.000 --> 00:01:46.850 align:middle line:84%
As soon as I change
my consciousness,

00:01:46.850 --> 00:01:50.330 align:middle line:84%
I see everything just as if
it were a motion picture.

00:01:50.330 --> 00:02:02.800 align:middle line:90%


00:02:02.800 --> 00:02:06.380 align:middle line:84%
>> I distinctly remember the
excitement of meeting Swami

00:02:06.380 --> 00:02:08.960 align:middle line:90%
Yogananda.

00:02:08.960 --> 00:02:11.902 align:middle line:90%
He was straight from the heart.

00:02:11.902 --> 00:02:15.160 align:middle line:84%
He looked strange, like
a woman with long hair.

00:02:15.160 --> 00:02:18.230 align:middle line:84%
But I remember
his powerful eyes.

00:02:18.230 --> 00:02:21.990 align:middle line:90%
He created such a stir.

00:02:21.990 --> 00:02:25.020 align:middle line:84%
>> I remember the first time
I heard Yogananda's voice.

00:02:25.020 --> 00:02:29.600 align:middle line:10%
I got a record, I think,
from SRF, and I put it on.

00:02:29.600 --> 00:02:31.810 align:middle line:10%
I didn't know what
to expect, you know?

00:02:31.810 --> 00:02:36.580 align:middle line:10%
And then this booming, powerful
(LOUDLY) I, Paramahansa

00:02:36.580 --> 00:02:39.010 align:middle line:10%
Yogananda, am singing.

00:02:39.010 --> 00:02:40.540 align:middle line:90%
Sing with me.

00:02:40.540 --> 00:02:42.940 align:middle line:90%
I went, aaaagh.

00:02:42.940 --> 00:02:47.940 align:middle line:10%
>> I, Paramahansa
Yogananda, am praying.

00:02:47.940 --> 00:02:49.580 align:middle line:10%
Pray with me.

00:02:49.580 --> 00:02:52.090 align:middle line:10%


00:02:52.090 --> 00:02:56.140 align:middle line:10%
Bless me, that with
the awakening dawn

00:02:56.140 --> 00:03:04.856 align:middle line:10%
I may awaken all souls with
my own and bring them to thee.

00:03:04.856 --> 00:03:08.272 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC - PARAMAHANSA YOGANANDA]

00:03:08.272 --> 00:03:13.640 align:middle line:90%


00:03:13.640 --> 00:03:15.430 align:middle line:84%
He wasn't trying
to sing prettily.

00:03:15.430 --> 00:03:17.890 align:middle line:84%
He wasn't trying to
entertain people.

00:03:17.890 --> 00:03:19.760 align:middle line:84%
He was singing,
you know, to God.

00:03:19.760 --> 00:03:22.570 align:middle line:90%
It was so powerful.

00:03:22.570 --> 00:03:25.640 align:middle line:84%
>> While I was in India,
I was with Ravi Shankar.

00:03:25.640 --> 00:03:29.650 align:middle line:10%
He gave me "Autobiography
of a Yogi."

00:03:29.650 --> 00:03:32.520 align:middle line:84%
I just looked at the
cover, and he just

00:03:32.520 --> 00:03:35.400 align:middle line:90%
zapped me with his eyes.

00:03:35.400 --> 00:03:38.170 align:middle line:84%
I mean, I can't imagine-- if
I hadn't read that, I probably

00:03:38.170 --> 00:03:40.894 align:middle line:90%
wouldn't have a life, really.

00:03:40.894 --> 00:03:42.560 align:middle line:84%
I probably would have
kicked the bucket,

00:03:42.560 --> 00:03:46.100 align:middle line:84%
or I'd just be, you know,
some horrible person,

00:03:46.100 --> 00:03:48.670 align:middle line:90%
have a pointless life.

00:03:48.670 --> 00:03:51.970 align:middle line:90%
It just gave meaning to life.

00:03:51.970 --> 00:03:55.294 align:middle line:84%
>> Steve Jobs apparently had
only one book on his iPad.

00:03:55.294 --> 00:03:56.710 align:middle line:10%
Lo and behold,
that book turns out

00:03:56.710 --> 00:03:58.830 align:middle line:10%
to be "The Autobiography
of a Yogi."

00:03:58.830 --> 00:04:10.310 align:middle line:90%


00:04:10.310 --> 00:04:14.120 align:middle line:84%
>> Yoga, for many, has become
something that you do with

00:04:14.120 --> 00:04:16.350 align:middle line:90%
your body.

00:04:16.350 --> 00:04:20.260 align:middle line:90%
But the yogis never taught that.

00:04:20.260 --> 00:04:23.920 align:middle line:84%
The way that Yogananda
taught yoga was use the body.

00:04:23.920 --> 00:04:25.450 align:middle line:90%
You have a body.

00:04:25.450 --> 00:04:31.000 align:middle line:10%
But it's really about the mind,
expanding your consciousness.

00:04:31.000 --> 00:04:32.260 align:middle line:90%
>> Who am I?

00:04:32.260 --> 00:04:33.200 align:middle line:90%
Who you are?

00:04:33.200 --> 00:04:37.020 align:middle line:84%
Why we came to this
Earth as a human?

00:04:37.020 --> 00:04:41.140 align:middle line:84%
>> It's really very easy to get
lost in the complexity of life.

00:04:41.140 --> 00:04:43.940 align:middle line:90%


00:04:43.940 --> 00:04:46.980 align:middle line:84%
>> We are conflicted
beings as humans.

00:04:46.980 --> 00:04:49.080 align:middle line:10%
One of the deepest
things about us

00:04:49.080 --> 00:04:51.665 align:middle line:10%
is that our lives don't make
sense except in the mystery.

00:04:51.665 --> 00:04:54.900 align:middle line:90%


00:04:54.900 --> 00:04:57.840 align:middle line:10%
>> Yogananda provided us
a vocabulary to talk about

00:04:57.840 --> 00:05:00.750 align:middle line:10%
the human spirit that got
away from dogma, and doctrine,

00:05:00.750 --> 00:05:01.550 align:middle line:10%
and ritual.

00:05:01.550 --> 00:05:07.803 align:middle line:90%


00:05:07.803 --> 00:05:11.050 align:middle line:84%
And whether it be a Hindu,
Muslim, Christian, Jewish--

00:05:11.050 --> 00:05:12.590 align:middle line:84%
whatever tradition
you're part of--

00:05:12.590 --> 00:05:16.120 align:middle line:84%
Yogananda charted a path
inward that connected you

00:05:16.120 --> 00:05:17.333 align:middle line:90%
with your own divinity.

00:05:17.333 --> 00:05:30.660 align:middle line:90%


00:05:30.660 --> 00:05:34.230 align:middle line:10%
>> Buried during the Dark
Ages, Kriya Yoga was revived

00:05:34.230 --> 00:05:38.610 align:middle line:10%
for modern man by the deathless
yogi Mahavatar Babaji.

00:05:38.610 --> 00:05:42.990 align:middle line:90%


00:05:42.990 --> 00:05:45.435 align:middle line:84%
Babaji instructed
Lahiri Mahasaya

00:05:45.435 --> 00:05:49.830 align:middle line:84%
to teach Kriya Yoga to
others, the transmission

00:05:49.830 --> 00:05:52.520 align:middle line:84%
of the ancient science
from guru to disciple.

00:05:52.520 --> 00:05:55.195 align:middle line:90%


00:05:55.195 --> 00:05:59.980 align:middle line:84%
Unknown to society in general,
a great spiritual Renaissance

00:05:59.980 --> 00:06:02.810 align:middle line:84%
started in a remote
corner of Banaras.

00:06:02.810 --> 00:06:05.810 align:middle line:90%


00:06:05.810 --> 00:06:09.262 align:middle line:90%
[CHATTER]

00:06:09.262 --> 00:06:17.070 align:middle line:90%


00:06:17.070 --> 00:06:20.486 align:middle line:90%
[CHIMES]

00:06:20.486 --> 00:06:21.462 align:middle line:90%


00:06:21.462 --> 00:06:25.910 align:middle line:84%
As the fragrance of flowers
cannot be suppressed,

00:06:25.910 --> 00:06:30.520 align:middle line:84%
so devotees from every part of
India began to seek the divine

00:06:30.520 --> 00:06:32.720 align:middle line:90%
nectar of this liberated master.

00:06:32.720 --> 00:06:39.510 align:middle line:90%


00:06:39.510 --> 00:06:43.770 align:middle line:10%
Day after day, the guru
initiated one or two devotees

00:06:43.770 --> 00:06:47.080 align:middle line:10%
into Kriya Yoga, the
science of meditation.

00:06:47.080 --> 00:06:49.780 align:middle line:90%


00:06:49.780 --> 00:06:56.280 align:middle line:84%
Early in their married life,
my parents became disciples.

00:06:56.280 --> 00:07:00.030 align:middle line:84%
Lahiri Mahasaya predicted
my birth and that

00:07:00.030 --> 00:07:02.430 align:middle line:84%
through this body
many shall receive

00:07:02.430 --> 00:07:06.740 align:middle line:84%
the spiritual
enlightenment of India.

00:07:06.740 --> 00:07:10.440 align:middle line:84%
The message of yoga will
encircle the globe, he said.

00:07:10.440 --> 00:07:14.150 align:middle line:84%
It will aid in establishing
the brotherhood of man.

00:07:14.150 --> 00:07:18.190 align:middle line:84%
But when I heard the word
guru, it frightened me.

00:07:18.190 --> 00:07:21.220 align:middle line:84%
For I knew what that
responsibility meant.

00:07:21.220 --> 00:07:24.670 align:middle line:90%


00:07:24.670 --> 00:07:28.120 align:middle line:84%
>> His great burden is to be
the representative of this

00:07:28.120 --> 00:07:32.330 align:middle line:90%
5,000-year-old tradition.

00:07:32.330 --> 00:07:35.380 align:middle line:84%
>> This is a man with
intuitive knowledge,

00:07:35.380 --> 00:07:40.600 align:middle line:84%
extraordinary yogic powers, and
he could perceive events that

00:07:40.600 --> 00:07:43.610 align:middle line:90%
were decades in front of him.

00:07:43.610 --> 00:07:46.910 align:middle line:84%
But his teachings
caused controversy.

00:07:46.910 --> 00:07:48.974 align:middle line:84%
>> He would be
called into question,

00:07:48.974 --> 00:07:50.765 align:middle line:84%
and everything he worked
for would unravel.

00:07:50.765 --> 00:07:54.516 align:middle line:90%


00:07:54.516 --> 00:07:57.450 align:middle line:90%
[WHISPERING VOICES]

00:07:57.450 --> 00:08:00.873 align:middle line:90%
[LOCOMOTIVE]

00:08:00.873 --> 00:08:12.140 align:middle line:90%


00:08:12.140 --> 00:08:14.120 align:middle line:90%
>> Every soul is on a journey.

00:08:14.120 --> 00:08:16.160 align:middle line:10%
People are at different
levels in that journey.

00:08:16.160 --> 00:08:27.110 align:middle line:90%


00:08:27.110 --> 00:08:29.960 align:middle line:10%
I think we all believe that
there's more to life than what

00:08:29.960 --> 00:08:31.050 align:middle line:10%
we experience every day.

00:08:31.050 --> 00:08:35.480 align:middle line:90%


00:08:35.480 --> 00:08:38.840 align:middle line:10%
>> Yogananda happens to be
what I would call a spiritual

00:08:38.840 --> 00:08:44.720 align:middle line:10%
prodigy, a spiritual genius,
which means he had access

00:08:44.720 --> 00:08:49.130 align:middle line:10%
to a domain of awareness that
most people don't have access

00:08:49.130 --> 00:08:50.440 align:middle line:10%
to.

00:08:50.440 --> 00:08:53.525 align:middle line:84%
Like mathematical
geniuses, he explored

00:08:53.525 --> 00:08:56.550 align:middle line:84%
a much larger territory
in the spiritual domain.

00:08:56.550 --> 00:09:00.370 align:middle line:90%


00:09:00.370 --> 00:09:04.900 align:middle line:84%
>> Sometimes, I used to
lapse into the consciousness

00:09:04.900 --> 00:09:05.960 align:middle line:90%
of my true spirit.

00:09:05.960 --> 00:09:08.510 align:middle line:90%


00:09:08.510 --> 00:09:11.900 align:middle line:84%
Clear recollections came
to me of a distant life

00:09:11.900 --> 00:09:16.760 align:middle line:84%
in which I had been a yogi
amid the Himalayan snows.

00:09:16.760 --> 00:09:19.430 align:middle line:84%
>> He also had visions
of seeing his guru.

00:09:19.430 --> 00:09:29.700 align:middle line:90%


00:09:29.700 --> 00:09:31.440 align:middle line:84%
Throughout the ages,
there have been

00:09:31.440 --> 00:09:34.380 align:middle line:84%
mystics who come with
special knowledge, that

00:09:34.380 --> 00:09:39.300 align:middle line:84%
helps us understand our
place in the Universe.

00:09:39.300 --> 00:09:42.390 align:middle line:84%
Yogananda was born at the
dawn of the Atomic Age, when

00:09:42.390 --> 00:09:44.610 align:middle line:84%
modern physics would
shatter our most

00:09:44.610 --> 00:09:48.180 align:middle line:84%
basic beliefs about
the nature of reality,

00:09:48.180 --> 00:09:51.450 align:middle line:84%
and paved the way for an
ancient and hidden teaching

00:09:51.450 --> 00:09:52.710 align:middle line:90%
to be received by many.

00:09:52.710 --> 00:09:55.830 align:middle line:90%


00:09:55.830 --> 00:10:00.720 align:middle line:84%
>> Yogananda had been told since
infancy by saints and seers

00:10:00.720 --> 00:10:03.850 align:middle line:84%
that he'd be taking these
teachings to the West.

00:10:03.850 --> 00:10:06.600 align:middle line:84%
But he thought, how
is this possible?

00:10:06.600 --> 00:10:10.050 align:middle line:84%
You know, it was absurd, because
he barely spoke any English.

00:10:10.050 --> 00:10:24.140 align:middle line:90%


00:10:24.140 --> 00:10:28.051 align:middle line:10%
>> One day, my mind
went away from Ranchi.

00:10:28.051 --> 00:10:31.270 align:middle line:84%
I went to the
storeroom to meditate,

00:10:31.270 --> 00:10:32.855 align:middle line:90%
and I fell into an ecstasy.

00:10:32.855 --> 00:10:40.188 align:middle line:90%


00:10:40.188 --> 00:10:43.667 align:middle line:90%
[RUMBLING]

00:10:43.667 --> 00:10:52.120 align:middle line:90%


00:10:52.120 --> 00:10:54.030 align:middle line:90%
America.

00:10:54.030 --> 00:10:56.090 align:middle line:84%
Surely, these people
are Americans.

00:10:56.090 --> 00:10:59.380 align:middle line:90%


00:10:59.380 --> 00:11:00.720 align:middle line:10%
>> It's scary to the mind.

00:11:00.720 --> 00:11:05.530 align:middle line:10%
I think the first thing
was, [EXHALES] oh my god.

00:11:05.530 --> 00:11:09.720 align:middle line:84%
>> Imagine in your own life
having a message so strong that

00:11:09.720 --> 00:11:11.610 align:middle line:84%
it totally changes
your life in a moment.

00:11:11.610 --> 00:11:16.670 align:middle line:90%


00:11:16.670 --> 00:11:19.770 align:middle line:10%
And at that time, he'd been
here about three years.

00:11:19.770 --> 00:11:21.640 align:middle line:84%
He probably thought
this was his life work.

00:11:21.640 --> 00:11:24.150 align:middle line:90%


00:11:24.150 --> 00:11:27.440 align:middle line:84%
>> I had founded a school,
following the educational

00:11:27.440 --> 00:11:30.760 align:middle line:84%
ideals of the rishis, whose
forest ashrams had been

00:11:30.760 --> 00:11:33.510 align:middle line:90%
the ancient seat of learning.

00:11:33.510 --> 00:11:36.290 align:middle line:84%
Overcoming restlessness
of the body and mind

00:11:36.290 --> 00:11:42.140 align:middle line:84%
by concentration techniques,
achieved astonishing results.

00:11:42.140 --> 00:11:44.120 align:middle line:10%
>> He established a
"How to Live" school.

00:11:44.120 --> 00:11:47.659 align:middle line:84%
I wish we had "How
to Live" schools.

00:11:47.659 --> 00:11:48.950 align:middle line:90%
You have to learn your grammar.

00:11:48.950 --> 00:11:51.690 align:middle line:84%
You have to learn your
math and your science.

00:11:51.690 --> 00:11:53.690 align:middle line:84%
But you also have to
learn how to live.

00:11:53.690 --> 00:11:59.297 align:middle line:10%
>> --and 1, 2, 3, 4, 5
[NON-ENGLISH SPEECH] 1, 2, 3,

00:11:59.297 --> 00:12:02.410 align:middle line:10%
4, 5 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

00:12:02.410 --> 00:12:04.450 align:middle line:90%
>> Ma'am, love conquers all.

00:12:04.450 --> 00:12:05.500 align:middle line:90%
>> Love conquers all.

00:12:05.500 --> 00:12:07.820 align:middle line:90%
Very good.

00:12:07.820 --> 00:12:09.950 align:middle line:84%
>> He's in love
with his country.

00:12:09.950 --> 00:12:12.292 align:middle line:84%
He is being respected
by his community.

00:12:12.292 --> 00:12:14.750 align:middle line:84%
He's seeing his vision manifest
where children are learning

00:12:14.750 --> 00:12:16.860 align:middle line:90%
the art and science of yoga.

00:12:16.860 --> 00:12:18.860 align:middle line:84%
And then he's sitting
there, and all of a sudden

00:12:18.860 --> 00:12:22.630 align:middle line:84%
he becomes aware that he
has to leave all of it.

00:12:22.630 --> 00:12:28.400 align:middle line:84%
>> God is taking
me away to America.

00:12:28.400 --> 00:12:31.460 align:middle line:84%
>> He never wanted
to come to America.

00:12:31.460 --> 00:12:34.770 align:middle line:84%
That was not part
of his dream at all.

00:12:34.770 --> 00:12:38.010 align:middle line:84%
Let me just go to the Himalayas
and just live in a cave there.

00:12:38.010 --> 00:12:39.300 align:middle line:90%
I can do good there.

00:12:39.300 --> 00:12:41.120 align:middle line:90%
I can pray for people.

00:12:41.120 --> 00:12:45.810 align:middle line:10%
But his teacher said no,
you must go to the West.

00:12:45.810 --> 00:12:46.800 align:middle line:90%
Go to America.

00:12:46.800 --> 00:12:49.700 align:middle line:90%


00:12:49.700 --> 00:12:53.440 align:middle line:10%
>> Tears stood in my eyes as I
cast a last look at the little

00:12:53.440 --> 00:12:58.330 align:middle line:10%
boys and the sunny
acres of Ranchi.

00:12:58.330 --> 00:13:01.565 align:middle line:84%
I knew henceforth I would
dwell in foreign lands.

00:13:01.565 --> 00:13:05.560 align:middle line:90%


00:13:05.560 --> 00:13:06.490 align:middle line:90%
[GUNSHOTS]

00:13:06.490 --> 00:13:06.770 align:middle line:84%
[MUSIC - SPIKE JONES
AND HIS CITY SLICKERS,

00:13:06.770 --> 00:13:07.570 align:middle line:90%
"THE CHARLESTON"]

00:13:07.570 --> 00:13:10.180 align:middle line:84%
(SINGING) Charleston,
Charleston, made in Carolina.

00:13:10.180 --> 00:13:12.570 align:middle line:90%
Some dance, some prance.

00:13:12.570 --> 00:13:15.516 align:middle line:10%
I'll say there's
nothing finer than--

00:13:15.516 --> 00:13:18.910 align:middle line:10%
[CLARINET SOLO]

00:13:18.910 --> 00:13:21.400 align:middle line:90%
>> How alone I was here.

00:13:21.400 --> 00:13:24.250 align:middle line:90%
Not a soul I knew.

00:13:24.250 --> 00:13:27.460 align:middle line:84%
I had heard many stories
about the materialistic West,

00:13:27.460 --> 00:13:32.410 align:middle line:84%
a land very
different from India.

00:13:32.410 --> 00:13:34.660 align:middle line:84%
It was somewhat of a
daunting experience

00:13:34.660 --> 00:13:36.610 align:middle line:90%
to go out on the streets.

00:13:36.610 --> 00:13:40.000 align:middle line:84%
My strange dress prompted
boyish mockery and--

00:13:40.000 --> 00:13:40.950 align:middle line:90%
and catcalls.

00:13:40.950 --> 00:13:42.040 align:middle line:90%
>> Who's that?

00:13:42.040 --> 00:13:44.590 align:middle line:84%
>> There were kids that
were throwing stones at him,

00:13:44.590 --> 00:13:46.584 align:middle line:90%
calling him names.

00:13:46.584 --> 00:13:49.480 align:middle line:84%
>> I think he was called
a magician at one point,

00:13:49.480 --> 00:13:51.670 align:middle line:90%
a snake charmer.

00:13:51.670 --> 00:13:56.020 align:middle line:84%
>> In 1920, many Americans were
still not used to having Jews

00:13:56.020 --> 00:13:57.220 align:middle line:90%
here.

00:13:57.220 --> 00:14:01.090 align:middle line:84%
And now comes a
darker-skinned swami

00:14:01.090 --> 00:14:02.890 align:middle line:90%
in orange robes and a turban.

00:14:02.890 --> 00:14:05.650 align:middle line:90%


00:14:05.650 --> 00:14:07.910 align:middle line:90%
>> I noticed some hot dog signs.

00:14:07.910 --> 00:14:12.086 align:middle line:10%
In imagination, I saw all kinds
of dogs going through the meat

00:14:12.086 --> 00:14:15.280 align:middle line:10%
chopper, and I
thought, my Lord, why

00:14:15.280 --> 00:14:17.890 align:middle line:10%
did you bring me to the
land where people eat dogs?

00:14:17.890 --> 00:14:23.340 align:middle line:90%


00:14:23.340 --> 00:14:25.060 align:middle line:10%
>> When Yogananda
came to United States,

00:14:25.060 --> 00:14:27.850 align:middle line:10%
it was after World War I. The
world was a very different

00:14:27.850 --> 00:14:29.040 align:middle line:10%
place.

00:14:29.040 --> 00:14:32.050 align:middle line:90%
It was a very powerful time.

00:14:32.050 --> 00:14:36.740 align:middle line:10%
>> There was this
upsurge of freedom--

00:14:36.740 --> 00:14:40.390 align:middle line:10%
freedom of sexuality,
freedom of expression.

00:14:40.390 --> 00:14:46.900 align:middle line:84%
Boundaries of known reality were
being shattered and penetrated.

00:14:46.900 --> 00:14:50.320 align:middle line:84%
You had the Einsteinian
revolution sort

00:14:50.320 --> 00:14:53.410 align:middle line:84%
of flowering into
quantum physics,

00:14:53.410 --> 00:14:55.840 align:middle line:84%
and it became clear
that the world

00:14:55.840 --> 00:14:57.640 align:middle line:90%
was not what it appeared to be.

00:14:57.640 --> 00:15:00.550 align:middle line:90%


00:15:00.550 --> 00:15:04.630 align:middle line:84%
>> Western philosophers are
talking about the death of God

00:15:04.630 --> 00:15:06.834 align:middle line:84%
and Yogananda says, it's
not about the death of God.

00:15:06.834 --> 00:15:08.250 align:middle line:84%
It's about the
reconceptualization

00:15:08.250 --> 00:15:10.800 align:middle line:90%
of the Divine.

00:15:10.800 --> 00:15:14.310 align:middle line:10%
>> It's significant that
Yogananda's first lecture

00:15:14.310 --> 00:15:17.340 align:middle line:10%
in America was called
the Science of Religion--

00:15:17.340 --> 00:15:22.110 align:middle line:10%
not Hinduism, because using
religious terminology,

00:15:22.110 --> 00:15:29.820 align:middle line:10%
in Western people's minds, would
place his offerings in a box.

00:15:29.820 --> 00:15:32.016 align:middle line:10%
But Self-Realization?

00:15:32.016 --> 00:15:33.270 align:middle line:90%
Oh.

00:15:33.270 --> 00:15:34.250 align:middle line:90%
Yoga?

00:15:34.250 --> 00:15:35.050 align:middle line:90%
Oh.

00:15:35.050 --> 00:15:37.930 align:middle line:90%
Those are universal.

00:15:37.930 --> 00:15:41.080 align:middle line:10%
>> The spine and the brain
are the altars of God.

00:15:41.080 --> 00:15:42.880 align:middle line:10%
That's where the
electricity of God

00:15:42.880 --> 00:15:46.290 align:middle line:10%
flows down into the nervous
system, into the world,

00:15:46.290 --> 00:15:50.030 align:middle line:10%
and the searchlights of your
senses are turned outwards.

00:15:50.030 --> 00:15:53.500 align:middle line:10%
But when you will reverse the
searchlights, through Kriya

00:15:53.500 --> 00:15:56.790 align:middle line:10%
Yoga, and be concentrated
in the spine,

00:15:56.790 --> 00:15:59.290 align:middle line:10%
you will behold the Maker.

00:15:59.290 --> 00:16:02.000 align:middle line:10%
That's what
Self-Realization teaches--

00:16:02.000 --> 00:16:05.410 align:middle line:10%
the technique of meditation,
recharging the body battery

00:16:05.410 --> 00:16:06.950 align:middle line:10%
with cosmic energy.

00:16:06.950 --> 00:16:12.440 align:middle line:10%
For it is not a creed
or dogma, but a science

00:16:12.440 --> 00:16:13.990 align:middle line:10%
of the soul and spirit.

00:16:13.990 --> 00:16:17.960 align:middle line:10%
How the soul descended from
the cosmic consciousness

00:16:17.960 --> 00:16:21.130 align:middle line:10%
into the earth, and
the body and the senses

00:16:21.130 --> 00:16:22.340 align:middle line:10%
is the purpose of this work.

00:16:22.340 --> 00:16:27.540 align:middle line:90%


00:16:27.540 --> 00:16:31.890 align:middle line:84%
>> Imagine hearing that
God is in your spine.

00:16:31.890 --> 00:16:37.600 align:middle line:90%
In 1920, it was radical.

00:16:37.600 --> 00:16:42.900 align:middle line:10%
It was a bold explanation of
where to go to experience God.

00:16:42.900 --> 00:16:46.085 align:middle line:90%


00:16:46.085 --> 00:16:51.840 align:middle line:84%
>> For me, God is still
a bit unfathomable.

00:16:51.840 --> 00:16:54.770 align:middle line:90%


00:16:54.770 --> 00:16:56.220 align:middle line:90%
>> She-- she's in everything.

00:16:56.220 --> 00:16:58.490 align:middle line:90%
She's in everyone.

00:16:58.490 --> 00:17:00.630 align:middle line:84%
>> If you call him
energy, that's fine.

00:17:00.630 --> 00:17:03.690 align:middle line:90%


00:17:03.690 --> 00:17:06.869 align:middle line:84%
>> Yogananda thought of
Self-Realization as a science.

00:17:06.869 --> 00:17:09.460 align:middle line:84%
He thought of Kriya
Yoga as a science.

00:17:09.460 --> 00:17:11.700 align:middle line:84%
Religion has a lot of
baggage, but a science

00:17:11.700 --> 00:17:13.630 align:middle line:84%
means that it's part of
a scientific process.

00:17:13.630 --> 00:17:14.490 align:middle line:90%
It's empirical.

00:17:14.490 --> 00:17:16.020 align:middle line:90%
You can test certain things.

00:17:16.020 --> 00:17:18.930 align:middle line:84%
And your own spiritual
practice and Self-Realization

00:17:18.930 --> 00:17:20.640 align:middle line:90%
is that scientific process.

00:17:20.640 --> 00:17:23.579 align:middle line:10%
>> An individual is sort
of an organized packet

00:17:23.579 --> 00:17:27.210 align:middle line:10%
of consciousness that is
part of a bigger ocean

00:17:27.210 --> 00:17:30.750 align:middle line:10%
of consciousness, in that when
you are meditating and going

00:17:30.750 --> 00:17:34.050 align:middle line:10%
deep within, such as in yoga,
your inner consciousness is

00:17:34.050 --> 00:17:38.320 align:middle line:10%
combining with that
higher consciousness.

00:17:38.320 --> 00:17:41.650 align:middle line:10%
>> You couldn't have described
to a Westerner what Yogananda

00:17:41.650 --> 00:17:44.170 align:middle line:10%
was teaching prior
to the 20th century.

00:17:44.170 --> 00:17:46.610 align:middle line:10%
There simply wasn't
a vocabulary for it.

00:17:46.610 --> 00:17:51.210 align:middle line:90%


00:17:51.210 --> 00:17:54.930 align:middle line:84%
The apparently solid body
is made up of these whirling

00:17:54.930 --> 00:17:57.660 align:middle line:84%
atoms, and protons,
and electrons,

00:17:57.660 --> 00:18:00.390 align:middle line:84%
and those are
composed of energy--

00:18:00.390 --> 00:18:03.000 align:middle line:90%
the basic substance of creation.

00:18:03.000 --> 00:18:06.630 align:middle line:84%
>> The body is potentially
vast and omnipresent.

00:18:06.630 --> 00:18:10.760 align:middle line:90%


00:18:10.760 --> 00:18:16.770 align:middle line:10%
This earth is nothing
but movies to me.

00:18:16.770 --> 00:18:20.312 align:middle line:10%
Just like the beam
of a motion picture,

00:18:20.312 --> 00:18:24.380 align:middle line:10%
so is everything made
of shadows and light.

00:18:24.380 --> 00:18:27.540 align:middle line:10%
That's what we are-- light
and shadows of the Lord,

00:18:27.540 --> 00:18:30.200 align:middle line:10%
nothing else than that.

00:18:30.200 --> 00:18:36.194 align:middle line:10%
There's one purpose--
to get to the beam.

00:18:36.194 --> 00:18:42.470 align:middle line:90%


00:18:42.470 --> 00:18:46.760 align:middle line:84%
>> But the doors of perception
don't often open with

00:18:46.760 --> 00:18:48.140 align:middle line:90%
the intellect.

00:18:48.140 --> 00:18:52.250 align:middle line:84%
Something very powerful has
to happen to shake us out

00:18:52.250 --> 00:18:53.100 align:middle line:90%
of our comfort zone.

00:18:53.100 --> 00:19:01.880 align:middle line:90%


00:19:01.880 --> 00:19:06.340 align:middle line:10%
>> It was in Bareilly
on a midnight.

00:19:06.340 --> 00:19:10.760 align:middle line:84%
As I slept beside father, I was
awakened by a peculiar flutter.

00:19:10.760 --> 00:19:14.400 align:middle line:90%


00:19:14.400 --> 00:19:16.590 align:middle line:84%
>> When he was
about 11 years old,

00:19:16.590 --> 00:19:19.770 align:middle line:84%
he and his father were
in northern India.

00:19:19.770 --> 00:19:22.260 align:middle line:84%
The family was
temporarily separated,

00:19:22.260 --> 00:19:24.120 align:middle line:84%
and his mother had
gone to Calcutta

00:19:24.120 --> 00:19:27.930 align:middle line:84%
to prepare for the wedding
of the eldest brother.

00:19:27.930 --> 00:19:31.705 align:middle line:84%
And unknown to them, she had
contracted Asiatic cholera.

00:19:31.705 --> 00:19:35.690 align:middle line:90%


00:19:35.690 --> 00:19:40.520 align:middle line:84%
>> He had a dream that night
that his mother came to him.

00:19:40.520 --> 00:19:43.175 align:middle line:84%
>> The flimsy curtains parted,
and I saw the beloved form

00:19:43.175 --> 00:19:44.754 align:middle line:90%
of my mother.

00:19:44.754 --> 00:19:49.815 align:middle line:84%
(WHISPERING) Rush to
Calcutta if you would see me.

00:19:49.815 --> 00:19:51.565 align:middle line:90%
The wraith-like figure vanished.

00:19:51.565 --> 00:19:54.200 align:middle line:90%


00:19:54.200 --> 00:19:55.010 align:middle line:90%
Mother is dying.

00:19:55.010 --> 00:20:03.600 align:middle line:90%


00:20:03.600 --> 00:20:06.595 align:middle line:84%
I collapsed into an
almost lifeless state.

00:20:06.595 --> 00:20:11.380 align:middle line:90%


00:20:11.380 --> 00:20:13.250 align:middle line:90%
>> A telegram arrived.

00:20:13.250 --> 00:20:15.110 align:middle line:84%
She had died in a
matter of hours.

00:20:15.110 --> 00:20:24.390 align:middle line:90%


00:20:24.390 --> 00:20:25.910 align:middle line:90%
>> What was the purpose of this?

00:20:25.910 --> 00:20:38.030 align:middle line:90%


00:20:38.030 --> 00:20:43.100 align:middle line:84%
Her solacing black eyes had
been my refuge in the trifling

00:20:43.100 --> 00:20:46.720 align:middle line:90%
tragedies of childhood.

00:20:46.720 --> 00:20:48.960 align:middle line:90%
>> Farewell, my child.

00:20:48.960 --> 00:20:50.610 align:middle line:84%
The cosmic mother
will protect you.

00:20:50.610 --> 00:20:55.910 align:middle line:90%


00:20:55.910 --> 00:20:58.820 align:middle line:84%
>> (ECHOING) It is I who
have watched over thee,

00:20:58.820 --> 00:21:03.695 align:middle line:84%
life after life, in the
tenderness of many mothers.

00:21:03.695 --> 00:21:06.870 align:middle line:90%


00:21:06.870 --> 00:21:14.645 align:middle line:84%
See in my gaze the two black
eyes, the lost, beautiful eyes

00:21:14.645 --> 00:21:15.445 align:middle line:90%
thou seekest.

00:21:15.445 --> 00:21:26.710 align:middle line:90%


00:21:26.710 --> 00:21:28.630 align:middle line:84%
>> I used to dream
in my childhood,

00:21:28.630 --> 00:21:30.960 align:middle line:84%
a tiger used to break
my leg at night.

00:21:30.960 --> 00:21:35.810 align:middle line:90%


00:21:35.810 --> 00:21:38.280 align:middle line:84%
Mother used to come running
with a candle and say,

00:21:38.280 --> 00:21:40.220 align:middle line:90%
you are dreaming!

00:21:40.220 --> 00:21:42.862 align:middle line:90%
Where is it broken?

00:21:42.862 --> 00:21:45.910 align:middle line:90%
And then I used to laugh.

00:21:45.910 --> 00:21:50.110 align:middle line:84%
From that time on, I was
watchful, even in dreams,

00:21:50.110 --> 00:21:53.302 align:middle line:84%
to separate the
unreal from the real.

00:21:53.302 --> 00:21:57.000 align:middle line:90%


00:21:57.000 --> 00:21:59.460 align:middle line:84%
>> Once he had
cracked open the door,

00:21:59.460 --> 00:22:03.210 align:middle line:84%
his world would
never be the same.

00:22:03.210 --> 00:22:06.040 align:middle line:84%
But it would take
time and many tests

00:22:06.040 --> 00:22:11.160 align:middle line:84%
before he would fully awaken
into this new reality.

00:22:11.160 --> 00:22:13.500 align:middle line:84%
>> Merciful mother
of the universe,

00:22:13.500 --> 00:22:16.590 align:middle line:84%
teach me thyself
through visions,

00:22:16.590 --> 00:22:18.630 align:middle line:90%
or through a guru sent by thee.

00:22:18.630 --> 00:22:27.079 align:middle line:90%


00:22:27.079 --> 00:22:31.660 align:middle line:84%
I hoped to find him at
the Himalayan snows,

00:22:31.660 --> 00:22:34.995 align:middle line:84%
the Master whose face often
appeared to me in visions.

00:22:34.995 --> 00:22:39.450 align:middle line:90%


00:22:39.450 --> 00:22:43.940 align:middle line:84%
I gazed searchingly about me
on any excursion from home

00:22:43.940 --> 00:22:45.800 align:middle line:84%
for the face of
my destined guru.

00:22:45.800 --> 00:22:54.030 align:middle line:90%


00:22:54.030 --> 00:22:57.960 align:middle line:84%
One day, I wiped my
tear-swollen face

00:22:57.960 --> 00:23:00.570 align:middle line:84%
and set out for the distant
marketplace in Banaras.

00:23:00.570 --> 00:23:06.420 align:middle line:90%


00:23:06.420 --> 00:23:08.280 align:middle line:84%
Something told me
to look behind.

00:23:08.280 --> 00:23:18.190 align:middle line:90%


00:23:18.190 --> 00:23:19.320 align:middle line:90%
I had seen him in dreams.

00:23:19.320 --> 00:23:22.270 align:middle line:90%


00:23:22.270 --> 00:23:27.960 align:middle line:84%
The face was the one I'd
seen in 1,000 visions,

00:23:27.960 --> 00:23:32.442 align:middle line:84%
holding a promise that I
had not fully understood.

00:23:32.442 --> 00:23:35.400 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:23:35.400 --> 00:23:44.770 align:middle line:90%


00:23:44.770 --> 00:23:47.640 align:middle line:84%
I came to know him long
before I met him in this life.

00:23:47.640 --> 00:23:52.440 align:middle line:90%


00:23:52.440 --> 00:23:54.840 align:middle line:90%
It was him.

00:23:54.840 --> 00:23:55.760 align:middle line:90%
It was my Master.

00:23:55.760 --> 00:24:02.450 align:middle line:90%


00:24:02.450 --> 00:24:05.940 align:middle line:90%
He said, I have been waiting.

00:24:05.940 --> 00:24:23.260 align:middle line:90%


00:24:23.260 --> 00:24:26.950 align:middle line:84%
>> A true guru is there
to lead you to yourself,

00:24:26.950 --> 00:24:32.680 align:middle line:84%
not to himself, to what we
are truly capable of, not just

00:24:32.680 --> 00:24:34.930 align:middle line:90%
the limited aspect of us.

00:24:34.930 --> 00:24:39.490 align:middle line:90%


00:24:39.490 --> 00:24:45.890 align:middle line:84%
>> The spiritual path
is farthest from easy.

00:24:45.890 --> 00:24:49.390 align:middle line:84%
It requires undoing
aspects of ourselves.

00:24:49.390 --> 00:24:52.870 align:middle line:90%


00:24:52.870 --> 00:24:56.280 align:middle line:84%
>> My guru could not be
bribed, even by love.

00:24:56.280 --> 00:25:03.830 align:middle line:90%


00:25:03.830 --> 00:25:07.610 align:middle line:84%
The hard core of egotism
is difficult to dislodge,

00:25:07.610 --> 00:25:08.840 align:middle line:90%
except rudely.

00:25:08.840 --> 00:25:11.425 align:middle line:90%


00:25:11.425 --> 00:25:17.290 align:middle line:84%
This flattening to the ego
treatment was hard to endure.

00:25:17.290 --> 00:25:20.560 align:middle line:84%
I sometimes felt that
metaphorically he

00:25:20.560 --> 00:25:25.100 align:middle line:84%
was discovering and uprooting
every diseased tooth in my jaw.

00:25:25.100 --> 00:25:31.580 align:middle line:90%


00:25:31.580 --> 00:25:35.960 align:middle line:84%
Many teachers will tell you
to believe and then put out

00:25:35.960 --> 00:25:37.010 align:middle line:90%
your eyes of reason.

00:25:37.010 --> 00:25:40.810 align:middle line:90%


00:25:40.810 --> 00:25:44.590 align:middle line:84%
My guru said, I want you to
keep your eyes of reason open.

00:25:44.590 --> 00:25:47.280 align:middle line:90%


00:25:47.280 --> 00:25:51.510 align:middle line:84%
In addition, I will open
in you the eye of wisdom.

00:25:51.510 --> 00:25:54.480 align:middle line:90%


00:25:54.480 --> 00:25:57.945 align:middle line:90%
[SITAR MUSIC]

00:25:57.945 --> 00:26:13.320 align:middle line:90%


00:26:13.320 --> 00:26:15.060 align:middle line:90%
>> Yoga for me is freedom.

00:26:15.060 --> 00:26:21.696 align:middle line:90%


00:26:21.696 --> 00:26:24.450 align:middle line:84%
>> The state of needing
nothing is yoga.

00:26:24.450 --> 00:26:29.250 align:middle line:90%


00:26:29.250 --> 00:26:30.910 align:middle line:90%
>> We become one with peace.

00:26:30.910 --> 00:26:32.860 align:middle line:90%
We become one with joy.

00:26:32.860 --> 00:26:35.210 align:middle line:90%
We become one with love.

00:26:35.210 --> 00:26:39.070 align:middle line:84%
And we realize that
that is our true nature.

00:26:39.070 --> 00:26:49.490 align:middle line:90%


00:26:49.490 --> 00:26:52.820 align:middle line:84%
>> How tirelessly
my Master labored,

00:26:52.820 --> 00:26:57.980 align:middle line:84%
that the boy Mukunda be
transformed into the monk

00:26:57.980 --> 00:26:58.880 align:middle line:90%
Yogananda.

00:26:58.880 --> 00:27:09.594 align:middle line:90%


00:27:09.594 --> 00:27:13.010 align:middle line:90%
[STREETCAR BELLS]

00:27:13.010 --> 00:27:17.940 align:middle line:84%
Three happy years were spent in
humble circumstances in Boston.

00:27:17.940 --> 00:27:22.610 align:middle line:84%
I gave public lectures,
taught classes, and addressed

00:27:22.610 --> 00:27:27.710 align:middle line:84%
clubs, colleges, churches, and
groups of every denomination.

00:27:27.710 --> 00:27:31.490 align:middle line:84%
>> But it took Yogananda a
few years to realize that he

00:27:31.490 --> 00:27:34.760 align:middle line:84%
wasn't in the right place for
this message to really take

00:27:34.760 --> 00:27:35.918 align:middle line:90%
off.

00:27:35.918 --> 00:27:39.411 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC - "HOORAY FOR HOLLYWOOD"]

00:27:39.411 --> 00:27:42.410 align:middle line:90%
[CAR HORNS]

00:27:42.410 --> 00:27:46.670 align:middle line:84%
>> In 1925, Yogananda
arrives in Los Angeles.

00:27:46.670 --> 00:27:49.010 align:middle line:84%
And on the first night,
according to the "L.A. Times,"

00:27:49.010 --> 00:27:52.160 align:middle line:84%
over 6,000 people
attend his talk.

00:27:52.160 --> 00:27:55.490 align:middle line:84%
That's double the capacity
of the auditorium.

00:27:55.490 --> 00:27:57.590 align:middle line:84%
Los Angeles is
this new frontier.

00:27:57.590 --> 00:28:00.740 align:middle line:84%
It's a place of possibility
of a new beginning.

00:28:00.740 --> 00:28:03.380 align:middle line:84%
Ideas of Asian
spirituality have permeated

00:28:03.380 --> 00:28:06.650 align:middle line:84%
the West Coast in a way that
they haven't on the East Coast.

00:28:06.650 --> 00:28:09.800 align:middle line:10%
>> People come to Los Angeles
often looking for something.

00:28:09.800 --> 00:28:12.335 align:middle line:10%
So there's this already
mind of a seeker.

00:28:12.335 --> 00:28:14.910 align:middle line:90%


00:28:14.910 --> 00:28:18.300 align:middle line:84%
>> Yogananda does a seven-night
speaker series at the L.A.

00:28:18.300 --> 00:28:20.160 align:middle line:90%
Philharmonic Auditorium.

00:28:20.160 --> 00:28:23.670 align:middle line:10%
>> People go just to see the
show and because he's exotic

00:28:23.670 --> 00:28:27.030 align:middle line:10%
and entertaining
